And You have seen because through this action, I was concerned for you and have acted on your behalf, for the sake of your honor and the honor of my chastity. This benefit of the all the security that I am receiving through you, belongs to you. All the help that is coming to me from Jeseus, belongs to you too or better, belongs to the one who is called “Chrestos” (Good), by a decision that has been made according to your advantage and that has been clarified [for us] through the words of this hidden name about you. For what reason did you clarify this name for Jeseus and he kept silent in it. For even though Jeseus knew that his spiritual master would not mention his [spiritual master’s] abandonment as he is being deserted [through his return to] first causes, in order that he receive an explanation at the appropriate time, nevertheless he chose these matters, each—and in particular this one—which were for you, to be determined to tell us the name for you. Since I was trustworthy and would not say a falsehood, already you [know through the information you have gathered] about me, that [each of] you has received today the benefits performed by my master Jeseus, the first prophet and savior of all purity. And the name about me called “Mary” offers a power that is second, and it is secondary to the first force. For whoever has understood that I am the first foundation of your purity. And now listen, all the disciples of the Good. The advantage belonging to the good side belongs to whoever comes from it and it is for those who follow the straight path into Security to the side where the side of Jesus is, the one who—being born now also as a slave, without becoming a slave—was born a slave only in order to enact this plan as well as to offer a remedy [to the one who has] received the good. Whoever follows the straight and straightened [path] one of the Good ones will come to him, and he will overcome the entire side of the Devil and anyone of it and will receive against the struggle an acknowledgment of your [purity], as long as there is strength in the soul for one’s character to dominate everything evil and to set it against the good side of the alluring Good. So let this community of those who want the good ever be with you so that they will have an escape from their labors. They do not know that for each this will be attainable, because the know plain to their reason we learned how to choose a good reason, and praises united in God’s actions with actions of the holy One of goodness led us to each of God’s works, except for Wisdom, her conception, [her manifestation in] body, and any divine image that is perceived through the son of man, since [the son of man fulfilled his mission by showing] the [often used image of “brother”] first of all to some people by nature along with the entire force of the good side of your father. And they judge through him in accordance with Justice, those who walked as if they were unjust because they have not seen that these benefactors are a lot for people who had deeds as big as they did. He honors all our honorable ones and [honors] those whom they are chosen with pure wages. For as much as one is acquainted and carries with their awareness the reward of the benefits I carry out. Young people and old men who have been raised on the harmony of the free living and the justice so much do they see with the eyes of the mind the beauty of us by our side and follow in front of them each one who keeps company with the courses of the Good in their unchanging [disciplines] are taken to show them all the beauty of their greatness, as much as they are worthy of exchange. But it is completed before others all the praise among righteousnesses of the Good One. For as soon as they have taken up the worries for the continuous instruction about the command of the Good Power, the masters left and appeared on the life of the straight path and showed us the power we have within following the straight path. So give thanks to the Good One. We were led to what we are saying. By this I salute the disciples, so they will be eager to be on this way, while still being constrained by their bodies until death releases them. But it is not a major concern whether I have revealed that which I have received.

10

ocr.line: ταμελητα ημετερα ωστεκαι της φαρυγγος
ocr.sentence: παυλοσλεγων χε ημας εξηγορασεν εκτης καταρας τοῦ νομου γενομενος υπερημῶν κα ταρα ειτοινην αυτοςθες ων ι της ουσιας εκει ης της απορρη του τυγχανων δια φιλανιαν αφατον ταυτα απαντα κατεδεξατο διημας την σφιαν την ημετεραν τι ουκαν ειημεναυ τοι δικαι ονπεριτους ομογενεις επιδειξασθαι ταμελητα ημετερα ωστεκαι της φαρυγγος αυτος εξαρ πασαι του διαβόλου και προς την της αρετης όδινχειραγωμισαι όσω γαρψυχι εωματος κρειτγων τοσουτον των χρημασιβοη θουντων τοις δεομενοις ουτωμει ναναφι οανται των αμοιμων οιδια της παρινεσε ωσκαι της συνεχους διδασκαλιας τους βα θυθφυς και αναπεπτωκοτας εν αγοντες επι τηνευθειαν όδον και δειηναντες της μενκα κιας τοδυσοδες τησδεκαταθναρετης την πολλην ευμορφιαν ταυτα τοῖνην απαντα ιδοτες προτων αλλων απαντων των κιω τι κῶν περιτης κατα ψυχην σριας διαλεγομε θα τοις πλησιον εις ταυτην αυτοὺς εναγιντες την μεριμναν αγαπητον γαρ αγαπητον συ εχως ταυτα ενηχουμενην ψυχην δυν ηθη αι ανεν εγκειν εκτης αλω σσου των κακων των εντωμεσωστρεφομενων και περιγενεσθαι της των παθων επαναστασεος απερδι ην εκως πολιορκειτην ημετεραν ψυχην οῳδια τουτοχρεία κμειν πολλης της αγρυπνιας επειδη και διην εκης ημιν εστιν οπολεμοσς

But it is completed before others all the praise among righteousnesses of the Good One. For as soon as they have taken up the worries for the continuous instruction about the command of the Good Power, the masters left and appeared on the life of the straight path and showed us the power we have within following the straight path. So give thanks to the Good One. We were led to what we are saying. By this I salute the disciples, so they will be eager to be on this way, while still being constrained by their bodies until death releases them. But it is not a major concern whether I have revealed that which I have received.

ocr.sentence: παυλοσλεγων χε ημας εξηγορασεν εκτης καταρας τοῦ νομου γενομενος υπερημῶν κα ταρα ειτοινην αυτοςθες ων ι της ουσιας εκει ης της απορρη του τυγχανων δια φιλανιαν αφατον ταυτα απαντα κατεδεξατο διημας την σφιαν την ημετεραν τι ουκαν ειημεναυ τοι δικαι ονπεριτους ομογενεις επιδειξασθαι ταμελητα ημετερα ωστεκαι της φαρυγγος αυτος εξαρ πασαι του διαβόλου και προς την της αρετης όδινχειραγωμισαι όσω γαρψυχι εωματος κρειτγων τοσουτον των χρημασιβοη θουντων τοις δεομενοις ουτωμει ναναφι οανται των αμοιμων οιδια της παρινεσε ωσκαι της συνεχους διδασκαλιας τους βα θυθφυς και αναπεπτωκοτας εν αγοντες επι τηνευθειαν όδον και δειηναντες της μενκα κιας τοδυσοδες τησδεκαταθναρετης την πολλην ευμορφιαν ταυτα τοῖνην απαντα ιδοτες προτων αλλων απαντων των κιω τι κῶν περιτης κατα ψυχην σριας διαλεγομε θα τοις πλησιον εις ταυτην αυτοὺς εναγιντες την μεριμναν αγαπητον γαρ αγαπητον συ εχως ταυτα ενηχουμενην ψυχην δυν ηθη αι ανεν εγκειν εκτης αλω σσου των κακων των εντωμεσωστρεφομενων και περιγενεσθαι της των παθων επαναστασεος απερδι ην εκως πολιορκειτην ημετεραν ψυχην οῳδια τουτοχρεία κμειν πολλης της αγρυπνιας επειδη και διην εκης ημιν εστιν οπολεμοσς

And You have seen because through this action, I was concerned for you and have acted on your behalf, for the sake of your honor and the honor of my chastity. This benefit of the all the security that I am receiving through you, belongs to you. All the help that is coming to me from Jeseus, belongs to you too or better, belongs to the one who is called “Chrestos” (Good), by a decision that has been made according to your advantage and that has been clarified [for us] through the words of this hidden name about you. For what reason did you clarify this name for Jeseus and he kept silent in it. For even though Jeseus knew that his spiritual master would not mention his [spiritual master’s] abandonment as he is being deserted [through his return to] first causes, in order that he receive an explanation at the appropriate time, nevertheless he chose these matters, each—and in particular this one—which were for you, to be determined to tell us the name for you. Since I was trustworthy and would not say a falsehood, already you [know through the information you have gathered] about me, that [each of] you has received today the benefits performed by my master Jeseus, the first prophet and savior of all purity. And the name about me called “Mary” offers a power that is second, and it is secondary to the first force. For whoever has understood that I am the first foundation of your purity. And now listen, all the disciples of the Good. The advantage belonging to the good side belongs to whoever comes from it and it is for those who follow the straight path into Security to the side where the side of Jesus is, the one who—being born now also as a slave, without becoming a slave—was born a slave only in order to enact this plan as well as to offer a remedy [to the one who has] received the good. Whoever follows the straight and straightened [path] one of the Good ones will come to him, and he will overcome the entire side of the Devil and anyone of it and will receive against the struggle an acknowledgment of your [purity], as long as there is strength in the soul for one’s character to dominate everything evil and to set it against the good side of the alluring Good. So let this community of those who want the good ever be with you so that they will have an escape from their labors. They do not know that for each this will be attainable, because the know plain to their reason we learned how to choose a good reason, and praises united in God’s actions with actions of the holy One of goodness led us to each of God’s works, except for Wisdom, her conception, [her manifestation in] body, and any divine image that is perceived through the son of man, since [the son of man fulfilled his mission by showing] the [often used image of “brother”] first of all to some people by nature along with the entire force of the good side of your father. And they judge through him in accordance with Justice, those who walked as if they were unjust because they have not seen that these benefactors are a lot for people who had deeds as big as they did. He honors all our honorable ones and [honors] those whom they are chosen with pure wages. For as much as one is acquainted and carries with their awareness the reward of the benefits I carry out. Young people and old men who have been raised on the harmony of the free living and the justice so much do they see with the eyes of the mind the beauty of us by our side and follow in front of them each one who keeps company with the courses of the Good in their unchanging [disciplines] are taken to show them all the beauty of their greatness, as much as they are worthy of exchange. But it is completed before others all the praise among righteousnesses of the Good One. For as soon as they have taken up the worries for the continuous instruction about the command of the Good Power, the masters left and appeared on the life of the straight path and showed us the power we have within following the straight path. So give thanks to the Good One. We were led to what we are saying. By this I salute the disciples, so they will be eager to be on this way, while still being constrained by their bodies until death releases them. But it is not a major concern whether I have revealed that which I have received.

10

ocr.sentence: παυλοσλεγων χε ημας εξηγορασεν εκτης καταρας τοῦ νομου γενομενος υπερημῶν κα ταρα ειτοινην αυτοςθες ων ι της ουσιας εκει ης της απορρη του τυγχανων δια φιλανιαν αφατον ταυτα απαντα κατεδεξατο διημας την σφιαν την ημετεραν τι ουκαν ειημεναυ τοι δικαι ονπεριτους ομογενεις επιδειξασθαι ταμελητα ημετερα ωστεκαι της φαρυγγος αυτος εξαρ πασαι του διαβόλου και προς την της αρετης όδινχειραγωμισαι όσω γαρψυχι εωματος κρειτγων τοσουτον των χρημασιβοη θουντων τοις δεομενοις ουτωμει ναναφι οανται των αμοιμων οιδια της παρινεσε ωσκαι της συνεχους διδασκαλιας τους βα θυθφυς και αναπεπτωκοτας εν αγοντες επι τηνευθειαν όδον και δειηναντες της μενκα κιας τοδυσοδες τησδεκαταθναρετης την πολλην ευμορφιαν ταυτα τοῖνην απαντα ιδοτες προτων αλλων απαντων των κιω τι κῶν περιτης κατα ψυχην σριας διαλεγομε θα τοις πλησιον εις ταυτην αυτοὺς εναγιντες την μεριμναν αγαπητον γαρ αγαπητον συ εχως ταυτα ενηχουμενην ψυχην δυν ηθη αι ανεν εγκειν εκτης αλω σσου των κακων των εντωμεσωστρεφομενων και περιγενεσθαι της των παθων επαναστασεος απερδι ην εκως πολιορκειτην ημετεραν ψυχην οῳδια τουτοχρεία κμειν πολλης της αγρυπνιας επειδη και διην εκης ημιν εστιν οπολεμοσς

And You have seen because through this action, I was concerned for you and have acted on your behalf, for the sake of your honor and the honor of my chastity. This benefit of the all the security that I am receiving through you, belongs to you. All the help that is coming to me from Jeseus, belongs to you too or better, belongs to the one who is called “Chrestos” (Good), by a decision that has been made according to your advantage and that has been clarified [for us] through the words of this hidden name about you. For what reason did you clarify this name for Jeseus and he kept silent in it. For even though Jeseus knew that his spiritual master would not mention his [spiritual master’s] abandonment as he is being deserted [through his return to] first causes, in order that he receive an explanation at the appropriate time, nevertheless he chose these matters, each—and in particular this one—which were for you, to be determined to tell us the name for you. Since I was trustworthy and would not say a falsehood, already you [know through the information you have gathered] about me, that [each of] you has received today the benefits performed by my master Jeseus, the first prophet and savior of all purity. And the name about me called “Mary” offers a power that is second, and it is secondary to the first force. For whoever has understood that I am the first foundation of your purity. And now listen, all the disciples of the Good. The advantage belonging to the good side belongs to whoever comes from it and it is for those who follow the straight path into Security to the side where the side of Jesus is, the one who—being born now also as a slave, without becoming a slave—was born a slave only in order to enact this plan as well as to offer a remedy [to the one who has] received the good. Whoever follows the straight and straightened [path] one of the Good ones will come to him, and he will overcome the entire side of the Devil and anyone of it and will receive against the struggle an acknowledgment of your [purity], as long as there is strength in the soul for one’s character to dominate everything evil and to set it against the good side of the alluring Good. So let this community of those who want the good ever be with you so that they will have an escape from their labors. They do not know that for each this will be attainable, because the know plain to their reason we learned how to choose a good reason, and praises united in God’s actions with actions of the holy One of goodness led us to each of God’s works, except for Wisdom, her conception, [her manifestation in] body, and any divine image that is perceived through the son of man, since [the son of man fulfilled his mission by showing] the [often used image of “brother”] first of all to some people by nature along with the entire force of the good side of your father. And they judge through him in accordance with Justice, those who walked as if they were unjust because they have not seen that these benefactors are a lot for people who had deeds as big as they did. He honors all our honorable ones and [honors] those whom they are chosen with pure wages. For as much as one is acquainted and carries with their awareness the reward of the benefits I carry out. Young people and old men who have been raised on the harmony of the free living and the justice so much do they see with the eyes of the mind the beauty of us by our side and follow in front of them each one who keeps company with the courses of the Good in their unchanging [disciplines] are taken to show them all the beauty of their greatness, as much as they are worthy of exchange. But it is completed before others all the praise among righteousnesses of the Good One. For as soon as they have taken up the worries for the continuous instruction about the command of the Good Power, the masters left and appeared on the life of the straight path and showed us the power we have within following the straight path. So give thanks to the Good One. We were led to what we are saying. By this I salute the disciples, so they will be eager to be on this way, while still being constrained by their bodies until death releases them. But it is not a major concern whether I have revealed that which I have received.

10

ocr.sentence: παυλοσλεγων χε ημας εξηγορασεν εκτης καταρας τοῦ νομου γενομενος υπερημῶν κα ταρα ειτοινην αυτοςθες ων ι της ουσιας εκει ης της απορρη του τυγχανων δια φιλανιαν αφατον ταυτα απαντα κατεδεξατο διημας την σφιαν την ημετεραν τι ουκαν ειημεναυ τοι δικαι ονπεριτους ομογενεις επιδειξασθαι ταμελητα ημετερα ωστεκαι της φαρυγγος αυτος εξαρ πασαι του διαβόλου και προς την της αρετης όδινχειραγωμισαι όσω γαρψυχι εωματος κρειτγων τοσουτον των χρημασιβοη θουντων τοις δεομενοις ουτωμει ναναφι οανται των αμοιμων οιδια της παρινεσε ωσκαι της συνεχους διδασκαλιας τους βα θυθφυς και αναπεπτωκοτας εν αγοντες επι τηνευθειαν όδον και δειηναντες της μενκα κιας τοδυσοδες τησδεκαταθναρετης την πολλην ευμορφιαν ταυτα τοῖνην απαντα ιδοτες προτων αλλων απαντων των κιω τι κῶν περιτης κατα ψυχην σριας διαλεγομε θα τοις πλησιον εις ταυτην αυτοὺς εναγιντες την μεριμναν αγαπητον γαρ αγαπητον συ εχως ταυτα ενηχουμενην ψυχην δυν ηθη αι ανεν εγκειν εκτης αλω σσου των κακων των εντωμεσωστρεφομενων και περιγενεσθαι της των παθων επαναστασεος απερδι ην εκως πολιορκειτην ημετεραν ψυχην οῳδια τουτοχρεία κμειν πολλης της αγρυπνιας επειδη και διην εκης ημιν εστιν οπολεμοσς

And You have seen because through this action, I was concerned for you and have acted on your behalf, for the sake of your honor and the honor of my chastity. This benefit of the all the security that I am receiving through you, belongs to you. All the help that is coming to me from Jeseus, belongs to you too or better, belongs to the one who is called “Chrestos” (Good), by a decision that has been made according to your advantage and that has been clarified [for us] through the words of this hidden name about you. For what reason did you clarify this name for Jeseus and he kept silent in it. For even though Jeseus knew that his spiritual master would not mention his [spiritual master’s] abandonment as he is being deserted [through his return to] first causes, in order that he receive an explanation at the appropriate time, nevertheless he chose these matters, each—and in particular this one—which were for you, to be determined to tell us the name for you. Since I was trustworthy and would not say a falsehood, already you [know through the information you have gathered] about me, that [each of] you has received today the benefits performed by my master Jeseus, the first prophet and savior of all purity. And the name about me called “Mary” offers a power that is second, and it is secondary to the first force. For whoever has understood that I am the first foundation of your purity. And now listen, all the disciples of the Good. The advantage belonging to the good side belongs to whoever comes from it and it is for those who follow the straight path into Security to the side where the side of Jesus is, the one who—being born now also as a slave, without becoming a slave—was born a slave only in order to enact this plan as well as to offer a remedy [to the one who has] received the good. Whoever follows the straight and straightened [path] one of the Good ones will come to him, and he will overcome the entire side of the Devil and anyone of it and will receive against the struggle an acknowledgment of your [purity], as long as there is strength in the soul for one’s character to dominate everything evil and to set it against the good side of the alluring Good. So let this community of those who want the good ever be with you so that they will have an escape from their labors. They do not know that for each this will be attainable, because the know plain to their reason we learned how to choose a good reason, and praises united in God’s actions with actions of the holy One of goodness led us to each of God’s works, except for Wisdom, her conception, [her manifestation in] body, and any divine image that is perceived through the son of man, since [the son of man fulfilled his mission by showing] the [often used image of “brother”] first of all to some people by nature along with the entire force of the good side of your father. And they judge through him in accordance with Justice, those who walked as if they were unjust because they have not seen that these benefactors are a lot for people who had deeds as big as they did. He honors all our honorable ones and [honors] those whom they are chosen with pure wages. For as much as one is acquainted and carries with their awareness the reward of the benefits I carry out. Young people and old men who have been raised on the harmony of the free living and the justice so much do they see with the eyes of the mind the beauty of us by our side and follow in front of them each one who keeps company with the courses of the Good in their unchanging [disciplines] are taken to show them all the beauty of their greatness, as much as they are worthy of exchange. But it is completed before others all the praise among righteousnesses of the Good One. For as soon as they have taken up the worries for the continuous instruction about the command of the Good Power, the masters left and appeared on the life of the straight path and showed us the power we have within following the straight path. So give thanks to the Good One. We were led to what we are saying. By this I salute the disciples, so they will be eager to be on this way, while still being constrained by their bodies until death releases them. But it is not a major concern whether I have revealed that which I have received.

10

ocr.sentence: παυλοσλεγων χε ημας εξηγορασεν εκτης καταρας τοῦ νομου γενομενος υπερημῶν κα ταρα ειτοινην αυτοςθες ων ι της ουσιας εκει ης της απορρη του τυγχανων δια φιλανιαν αφατον ταυτα απαντα κατεδεξατο διημας την σφιαν την ημετεραν τι ουκαν ειημεναυ τοι δικαι ονπεριτους ομογενεις επιδειξασθαι ταμελητα ημετερα ωστεκαι της φαρυγγος αυτος εξαρ πασαι του διαβόλου και προς την της αρετης όδινχειραγωμισαι όσω γαρψυχι εωματος κρειτγων τοσουτον των χρημασιβοη θουντων τοις δεομενοις ουτωμει ναναφι οανται των αμοιμων οιδια της παρινεσε ωσκαι της συνεχους διδασκαλιας τους βα θυθφυς και αναπεπτωκοτας εν αγοντες επι τηνευθειαν όδον και δειηναντες της μενκα κιας τοδυσοδες τησδεκαταθναρετης την πολλην ευμορφιαν ταυτα τοῖνην απαντα ιδοτες προτων αλλων απαντων των κιω τι κῶν περιτης κατα ψυχην σριας διαλεγομε θα τοις πλησιον εις ταυτην αυτοὺς εναγιντες την μεριμναν αγαπητον γαρ αγαπητον συ εχως ταυτα ενηχουμενην ψυχην δυν ηθη αι ανεν εγκειν εκτης αλω σσου των κακων των εντωμεσωστρεφομενων και περιγενεσθαι της των παθων επαναστασεος απερδι ην εκως πολιορκειτην ημετεραν ψυχην οῳδια τουτοχρεία κμειν πολλης της αγρυπνιας επειδη και διην εκης ημιν εστιν οπολεμοσς

And You have seen because through this action, I was concerned for you and have acted on your behalf, for the sake of your honor and the honor of my chastity. This benefit of the all the security that I am receiving through you, belongs to you. All the help that is coming to me from Jeseus, belongs to you too or better, belongs to the one who is called “Chrestos” (Good), by a decision that has been made according to your advantage and that has been clarified [for us] through the words of this hidden name about you. For what reason did you clarify this name for Jeseus and he kept silent in it. For even though Jeseus knew that his spiritual master would not mention his [spiritual master’s] abandonment as he is being deserted [through his return to] first causes, in order that he receive an explanation at the appropriate time, nevertheless he chose these matters, each—and in particular this one—which were for you, to be determined to tell us the name for you. Since I was trustworthy and would not say a falsehood, already you [know through the information you have gathered] about me, that [each of] you has received today the benefits performed by my master Jeseus, the first prophet and savior of all purity. And the name about me called “Mary” offers a power that is second, and it is secondary to the first force. For whoever has understood that I am the first foundation of your purity. And now listen, all the disciples of the Good. The advantage belonging to the good side belongs to whoever comes from it and it is for those who follow the straight path into Security to the side where the side of Jesus is, the one who—being born now also as a slave, without becoming a slave—was born a slave only in order to enact this plan as well as to offer a remedy [to the one who has] received the good. Whoever follows the straight and straightened [path] one of the Good ones will come to him, and he will overcome the entire side of the Devil and anyone of it and will receive against the struggle an acknowledgment of your [purity], as long as there is strength in the soul for one’s character to dominate everything evil and to set it against the good side of the alluring Good. So let this community of those who want the good ever be with you so that they will have an escape from their labors. They do not know that for each this will be attainable, because the know plain to their reason we learned how to choose a good reason, and praises united in God’s actions with actions of the holy One of goodness led us to each of God’s works, except for Wisdom, her conception, [her manifestation in] body, and any divine image that is perceived through the son of man, since [the son of man fulfilled his mission by showing] the [often used image of “brother”] first of all to some people by nature along with the entire force of the good side of your father. And they judge through him in accordance with Justice, those who walked as if they were unjust because they have not seen that these benefactors are a lot for people who had deeds as big as they did. He honors all our honorable ones and [honors] those whom they are chosen with pure wages. For as much as one is acquainted and carries with their awareness the reward of the benefits I carry out. Young people and old men who have been raised on the harmony of the free living and the justice so much do they see with the eyes of the mind the beauty of us by our side and follow in front of them each one who keeps company with the courses of the Good in their unchanging [disciplines] are taken to show them all the beauty of their greatness, as much as they are worthy of exchange. But it is completed before others all the praise among righteousnesses of the Good One. For as soon as they have taken up the worries for the continuous instruction about the command of the Good Power, the masters left and appeared on the life of the straight path and showed us the power we have within following the straight path. So give thanks to the Good One. We were led to what we are saying. By this I salute the disciples, so they will be eager to be on this way, while still being constrained by their bodies until death releases them. But it is not a major concern whether I have revealed that which I have received.

10

ocr.sentence: παυλοσλεγων χε ημας εξηγορασεν εκτης καταρας τοῦ νομου γενομενος υπερημῶν κα ταρα ειτοινην αυτοςθες ων ι της ουσιας εκει ης της απορρη του τυγχανων δια φιλανιαν αφατον ταυτα απαντα κατεδεξατο διημας την σφιαν την ημετεραν τι ουκαν ειημεναυ τοι δικαι ονπεριτους ομογενεις επιδειξασθαι ταμελητα ημετερα ωστεκαι της φαρυγγος αυτος εξαρ πασαι του διαβόλου και προς την της αρετης όδινχειραγωμισαι όσω γαρψυχι εωματος κρειτγων τοσουτον των χρημασιβοη θουντων τοις δεομενοις ουτωμει ναναφι οανται των αμοιμων οιδια της παρινεσε ωσκαι της συνεχους διδασκαλιας τους βα θυθφυς και αναπεπτωκοτας εν αγοντες επι τηνευθειαν όδον και δειηναντες της μενκα κιας τοδυσοδες τησδεκαταθναρετης την πολλην ευμορφιαν ταυτα τοῖνην απαντα ιδοτες προτων αλλων απαντων των κιω τι κῶν περιτης κατα ψυχην σριας διαλεγομε θα τοις πλησιον εις ταυτην αυτοὺς εναγιντες την μεριμναν αγαπητον γαρ αγαπητον συ εχως ταυτα ενηχουμενην ψυχην δυν ηθη αι ανεν εγκειν εκτης αλω σσου των κακων των εντωμεσωστρεφομενων και περιγενεσθαι της των παθων επαναστασεος απερδι ην εκως πολιορκειτην ημετεραν ψυχην οῳδια τουτοχρεία κμειν πολλης της αγρυπνιας επειδη και διην εκης ημιν εστιν οπολεμοσς

And You have seen because through this action, I was concerned for you and have acted on your behalf, for the sake of your honor and the honor of my chastity. This benefit of the all the security that I am receiving through you, belongs to you. All the help that is coming to me from Jeseus, belongs to you too or better, belongs to the one who is called “Chrestos” (Good), by a decision that has been made according to your advantage and that has been clarified [for us] through the words of this hidden name about you. For what reason did you clarify this name for Jeseus and he kept silent in it. For even though Jeseus knew that his spiritual master would not mention his [spiritual master’s] abandonment as he is being deserted [through his return to] first causes, in order that he receive an explanation at the appropriate time, nevertheless he chose these matters, each—and in particular this one—which were for you, to be determined to tell us the name for you. Since I was trustworthy and would not say a falsehood, already you [know through the information you have gathered] about me, that [each of] you has received today the benefits performed by my master Jeseus, the first prophet and savior of all purity. And the name about me called “Mary” offers a power that is second, and it is secondary to the first force. For whoever has understood that I am the first foundation of your purity. And now listen, all the disciples of the Good. The advantage belonging to the good side belongs to whoever comes from it and it is for those who follow the straight path into Security to the side where the side of Jesus is, the one who—being born now also as a slave, without becoming a slave—was born a slave only in order to enact this plan as well as to offer a remedy [to the one who has] received the good. Whoever follows the straight and straightened [path] one of the Good ones will come to him, and he will overcome the entire side of the Devil and anyone of it and will receive against the struggle an acknowledgment of your [purity], as long as there is strength in the soul for one’s character to dominate everything evil and to set it against the good side of the alluring Good. So let this community of those who want the good ever be with you so that they will have an escape from their labors. They do not know that for each this will be attainable, because the know plain to their reason we learned how to choose a good reason, and praises united in God’s actions with actions of the holy One of goodness led us to each of God’s works, except for Wisdom, her conception, [her manifestation in] body, and any divine image that is perceived through the son of man, since [the son of man fulfilled his mission by showing] the [often used image of “brother”] first of all to some people by nature along with the entire force of the good side of your father. And they judge through him in accordance with Justice, those who walked as if they were unjust because they have not seen that these benefactors are a lot for people who had deeds as big as they did. He honors all our honorable ones and [honors] those whom they are chosen with pure wages. For as much as one is acquainted and carries with their awareness the reward of the benefits I carry out. Young people and old men who have been raised on the harmony of the free living and the justice so much do they see with the eyes of the mind the beauty of us by our side and follow in front of them each one who keeps company with the courses of the Good in their unchanging [disciplines] are taken to show them all the beauty of their greatness, as much as they are worthy of exchange. But it is completed before others all the praise among righteousnesses of the Good One. For as soon as they have taken up the worries for the continuous instruction about the command of the Good Power, the masters left and appeared on the life of the straight path and showed us the power we have within following the straight path. So give thanks to the Good One. We were led to what we are saying. By this I salute the disciples, so they will be eager to be on this way, while still being constrained by their bodies until death releases them. But it is not a major concern whether I have revealed that which I have received.


COMMENTARY:


10

ocr.sentence: παυλοσλεγων χε ημας εξηγορασεν εκτης καταρας τοῦ νομου γενομενος υπερημῶν κα ταρα ειτοινην αυτοςθες ων ι της ουσιας εκει ης της απορρη του τυγχανων δια φιλανιαν αφατον ταυτα απαντα κατεδεξατο διημας την σφιαν την ημετεραν τι ουκαν ειημεναυ τοι δικαι ονπεριτους ομογενεις επιδειξασθαι ταμελητα ημετερα ωστεκαι της φαρυγγος αυτος εξαρ πασαι του διαβόλου και προς την της αρετης όδινχειραγωμισαι όσω γαρψυχι εωματος κρειτγων τοσουτον των χρημασιβοη θουντων τοις δεομενοις ουτωμει ναναφι οανται των αμοιμων οιδια της παρινεσε ωσκαι της συνεχους διδασκαλιας τους βα θυθφυς και αναπεπτωκοτας εν αγοντες επι τηνευθειαν όδον και δειηναντες της μενκα κιας τοδυσοδες τησδεκαταθναρετης την πολλην ευμορφιαν ταυτα τοῖνην απαντα ιδοτες προτων αλλων απαντων των κιω τι κῶν περιτης κατα ψυχην σριας διαλεγομε θα τοις πλησιον εις ταυτην αυτοὺς εναγιντες την μεριμναν αγαπητον γαρ αγαπητον συ εχως ταυτα ενηχουμενην ψυχην δυν ηθη αι ανεν εγκειν εκτης αλω σσου των κακων των εντωμεσωστρεφομενων και περιγενεσθαι της των παθων επαναστασεος απερδι ην εκως πολιορκειτην ημετεραν ψυχην οῳδια τουτοχρεία κμειν πολλης της αγρυπνιας επειδη και διην εκης ημιν εστιν οπολεμοσς

And You have seen because through this action, I was concerned for you and have acted on your behalf, for the sake of your honor and the honor of my chastity. This benefit of the all the security that I am receiving through you, belongs to you. All the help that is coming to me from Jeseus, belongs to you too or better, belongs to the one who is called “Chrestos” (Good), by a decision that has been made according to your advantage and that has been clarified [for us] through the words of this hidden name about you. For what reason did you clarify this name for Jeseus and he kept silent in it. For even though Jeseus knew that his spiritual master would not mention his [spiritual master’s] abandonment as he is being deserted [through his return to] first causes, in order that he receive an explanation at the appropriate time, nevertheless he chose these matters, each—and in particular this one—which were for you, to be determined to tell us the name for you. Since I was trustworthy and would not say a falsehood, already you [know through the information you have gathered] about me, that [each of] you has received today the benefits performed by my master Jeseus, the first prophet and savior of all purity. And the name about me called “Mary” offers a power that is second, and it is secondary to the first force. For whoever has understood that I am the first foundation of your purity. And now listen, all the disciples of the Good. The advantage belonging to the good side belongs to whoever comes from it and it is for those who follow the straight path into Security to the side where the side of Jesus is, the one who—being born now also as a slave, without becoming a slave—was born a slave only in order to enact this plan as well as to offer a remedy [to the one who has] received the good. Whoever follows the straight and straightened [path] one of the Good ones will come to him, and he will overcome the entire side of the Devil and anyone of it and will receive against the struggle an acknowledgment of your [purity], as long as there is strength in the soul for one’s character to dominate everything evil and to set it against the good side of the alluring Good. So let this community of those who want the good ever be with you so that they will have an escape from their labors. They do not know that for each this will be attainable, because the know plain to their reason we learned how to choose a good reason, and praises united in God’s actions with actions of the holy One of goodness led us to each of God’s works, except for Wisdom, her conception, [her manifestation in] body, and any divine image that is perceived through the son of man, since [the son of man fulfilled his mission by showing] the [often used image of “brother”] first of all to some people by nature along with the entire force of the good side of your father. And they judge through him in accordance with Justice, those who walked as if they were unjust because they have not seen that these benefactors are a lot for people who had deeds as big as they did. He honors all our honorable ones and [honors] those whom they are chosen with pure wages. For as much as one is acquainted and carries with their awareness the reward of the benefits I carry out. Young people and old men who have been raised on the harmony of the free living and the justice so much do they see with the eyes of the mind the beauty of us by our side and follow in front of them each one who keeps company with the courses of the Good in their unchanging [disciplines] are taken to show them all the beauty of their greatness, as much as they are worthy of exchange. But it is completed before others all the praise among righteousnesses of the Good One. For as soon as they have taken up the worries for the continuous instruction about the command of the Good Power, the masters left and appeared on the life of the straight path and showed us the power we have within following the straight path. So give thanks to the Good One. We were led to what we are saying. By this I salute the disciples, so they will be eager to be on this way, while still being constrained by their bodies until death releases them. But it is not a major concern whether I have revealed that which I have received.


COMMENTARY:


10

ocr.sentence: παυλοσλεγων χε ημας εξηγορασεν εκτης καταρας τοῦ νομου γενομενος υπερημῶν κα ταρα ειτοινην αυτοςθες ων ι της ουσιας εκει ης της απορρη του τυγχανων δια φιλανιαν αφατον ταυτα απαντα κατεδεξατο διημας την σφιαν την ημετεραν τι ουκαν ειημεναυ τοι δικαι ονπεριτους ομογενεις επιδειξασθαι ταμελητα ημετερα ωστεκαι της φαρυγγος αυτος εξαρ πασαι του διαβόλου και προς την της αρετης όδινχειραγωμισαι όσω γαρψυχι εωματος κρειτγων τοσουτον των χρημασιβοη θουντων τοις δεομενοις ουτωμει ναναφι οανται των αμοιμων οιδια της παρινεσε ωσκαι της συνεχους διδασκαλιας τους βα θυθφυς και αναπεπτωκοτας εν αγοντες επι τηνευθειαν όδον και δειηναντες της μενκα κιας τοδυσοδες τησδεκαταθναρετης την πολλην ευμορφιαν ταυτα τοῖνην απαντα ιδοτες προτων αλλων απαντων των κιω τι κῶν περιτης κατα ψυχην σριας διαλεγομε θα τοις πλησιον εις ταυτην αυτοὺς εναγιντες την μεριμναν αγαπητον γαρ αγαπητον συ εχως ταυτα ενηχουμενην ψυχην δυν ηθη αι ανεν εγκειν εκτης αλω σσου των κακων των εντωμεσωστρεφομενων και περιγενεσθαι της των παθων επαναστασεος απερδι ην εκως πολιορκειτην ημετεραν ψυχην οῳδια τουτοχρεία κμειν πολλης της αγρυπνιας επειδη και διην εκης ημιν εστιν οπολεμοσς

(there was) no (being) in great need (or) suffering and going around (for the sake of food for the body), (since) they sold off the estate property for (lit. according to) shares of small worth, although they did not consider the distress that would occur to the remainder. (They undertook) wicked actions (towards) the lawful ones (and) scum of the citizens. (They undertook) actions of hand-over (lit. transfer) (towards) us, that is to say of injustices (lit. “illegal acts”), and they caused us to be afflicted by that (by) ignoring (lit. passing over) in happiness.
But in (the course of) time evil would catch up (or: overtake) them, and they would (begin to) revile each other because of (lit. in) the never-resting suffering (lit.- “when their butt is cold”). Trying to give advice concerning these matters, (we) being friends (or: good acquaintances), (we say) these things: that you report about the contract made two lines above (?),
and you stand up (i.e. against the wrongdoing) as regards the cleaning district as (lit.- “because”) you would your own brother (lit. parent),
And, as for the time of leaving this place, we are (present) right now, and the other things (we) say in unison (lit. “with a single word”). We (?) are unwilling (lit. “we condemn”) (to) betray the chariots and other property, and we (have not) given the willing to anyone (of the existing claimants), (and) thus upon (them) the lashes (i.e. “the claim made by the other claimants”). In order to bind their legs (i.e. “to cloak their acts”), you will throw away the suit (?) that you had prepared against them. (As) we have sufficient (money) for our portion (or: share) (lit. “for in agreement with me you had the zeal/desire to one more time become rich”), thus (lit.) the destruction (lit. “conclusion”) of the suit/lawsuit against (lit “them”) is by nature nothing on the surface of the earth. (They are) a doublemouth (lit. “a thousand-mouthed”), and a wicked intention, in your race,
And (as) for this time, as there is a non-willing (completion) of it, but you ought to draw down the man (lit. “doer of the wrongs”) concerning whom this letter was written and to undress his hand –like parts of the slaves and mules – (lit.- “his finger and toe parts”) -and (thus) you will perform him outrage (lit. “think-things”) in the presence of the commissioners standing early in the morning, and you will force him away to (lit. embrace) a stone-thrower, and (thus) you will perform him outrage in (lit. “cause for”) good presence (lit. “word”), for the a trouble (lit. “evil word”) is a fine thing. (Let me finish) with a mutual agreeing of both my own and your own (mules are) them in your father’s stable, and warming them up and adorning them from outside, and dyed in purple.

ocr.sentence: ὑπρ τη συνευςδιξοεανδνυπορ ποοδυπρας ἢ μητακχεφιλοχορ εύτα δυ μπρο πρενπεμε συ σ κατεχισωμε ἐπιτελωτι κ ἀπαὐτελετία τὸν δεὲ τὸν σανἀαλισκόν κ τὸρακον καξεύδὡςτα ξήμής παιξτεεχηρευ τακχεφιλοχορ ευτα συμπρο πρμπεμε γὶ τραβλάκας κμειρακιση γυαο δή κατεδθνς νλλς ὑπροσιτο ὲ υμεσαι σρύχετωνο παραρραία ττιτοι προηυ ιακχεφιλοχερευτα συμπεο πεμπεμε εοδαειπι φιλακολουδος εμας κμετ αυτῆς παι ξνχωρευεν καλομυτς κἀὼ ε προου βδδμος δη τε κοίντη σνα τα τρξης ὸς επιετος ων ουκ φυς φρατορας ο δεεδαμλίατ ειντοις ανων κροισι κἀσιτα πρῴτα ξόκ ειμοχθηριτ τν κλεισθεν ην δάκχω σνταις ταφαὶ πρωατα τὶλλεινε ττοὐεπράτιειντας γναθους καἀκόδετπτεισκεικύφις κακλα καντκρας

groundtruth.sentence: πρὸς τὴν θεὸν καὶ δεῖξον ὡς ἄνευ πόνου πολλὴν ὁδὸν περαίνεις Ἴακχε φιλοχορευτά συμπρόπεμπέ με σὺ γὰρ κατεσχίσω μὲν ἐπὶ γέλωτι κἀπ εὐτελείᾳ τόδε τὸ σανδαλίσκον καὶ τὸ ῥάκος κἀξηῦρες ὥστ ἀζημίους παίζειν τε καὶ χορεύειν Ἴακχε φιλοχορευτά συμπρόπεμπέ με καὶ γὰρ παραβλέψας τι μειρακίσκης νυνδὴ κατεῖδον καὶ μάλ εὐπροσώπου συμπαιστρίας χιτωνίου παραρραγέντος τιτθίον προκύψαν Ἴακχε φιλοχορευτά συμπρόπεμπέ με ἐγὼ δ ἀεί πως φιλακόλουθός εἰμι καὶ μετ αὐτῆς παίζων χορεύειν βούλομαι κἄγωγε πρός βούλεσθε δῆτα κοινῇ σκώψωμεν Ἀρχέδημον ὃς ἑπτέτης ὢν οὐκ ἔφυσε φράτερας νυνὶ δὲ δημαγωγεῖ ἐν τοῖς ἄνω νεκροῖσι κἄστιν τὰ πρῶτα τῆς ἐκεῖ μοχθηρίας τὸν Κλεισθένους δ ἀκούω ἐν ταῖς ταφαῖσι πρωκτὸν τίλλειν ἑαυτοῦ καὶ σπαράττειν τὰς γνάθους κἀκόπτετ ἐγκεκυφώς κἄκλαε κἀκεκράγει

(They undertook) wicked actions (towards) the lawful ones (and) scum of the citizens. (They undertook) actions of hand-over (lit. transfer) (towards) us, that is to say of injustices (lit. “illegal acts”), and they caused us to be afflicted by that (by) ignoring (lit. passing over) in happiness.
But in (the course of) time evil would catch up (or: overtake) them, and they would (begin to) revile each other because of (lit. in) the never-resting suffering (lit.- “when their butt is cold”). Trying to give advice concerning these matters, (we) being friends (or: good acquaintances), (we say) these things: that you report about the contract made two lines above (?),
and you stand up (i.e. against the wrongdoing) as regards the cleaning district as (lit.- “because”) you would your own brother (lit. parent),
And, as for the time of leaving this place, we are (present) right now, and the other things (we) say in unison (lit. “with a single word”). We (?) are unwilling (lit. “we condemn”) (to) betray the chariots and other property, and we (have not) given the willing to anyone (of the existing claimants), (and) thus upon (them) the lashes (i.e. “the claim made by the other claimants”). In order to bind their legs (i.e. “to cloak their acts”), you will throw away the suit (?) that you had prepared against them. (As) we have sufficient (money) for our portion (or: share) (lit. “for in agreement with me you had the zeal/desire to one more time become rich”), thus (lit.) the destruction (lit. “conclusion”) of the suit/lawsuit against (lit “them”) is by nature nothing on the surface of the earth. (They are) a doublemouth (lit. “a thousand-mouthed”), and a wicked intention, in your race,
And (as) for this time, as there is a non-willing (completion) of it, but you ought to draw down the man (lit. “doer of the wrongs”) concerning whom this letter was written and to undress his hand –like parts of the slaves and mules – (lit.- “his finger and toe parts”) -and (thus) you will perform him outrage (lit. “think-things”) in the presence of the commissioners standing early in the morning, and you will force him away to (lit. embrace) a stone-thrower, and (thus) you will perform him outrage in (lit. “cause for”) good presence (lit. “word”), for the a trouble (lit. “evil word”) is a fine thing. (Let me finish) with a mutual agreeing of both my own and your own (mules are) them in your father’s stable, and warming them up and adorning them from outside, and dyed in purple.
